 <body>
  <h1>
   <br/><img src="https://gms.magecorn.com/Manual/assets/Images/Scripting_Reference/Drag_And_Drop/Reference/Time_Sources/Action_Icons/BPM_to_Seconds.png"/><br/>
   BPM to Seconds
  </h1>
  This action takes a beats-per-minute value, and returns the length of each beat in seconds.
   
   
    This can be used when
  <a href="Create_Time_Source.htm">
   creating a Time Source
  </a>
  to use a BPM value for the
  <span>
   Time Source
  </span>
  . It's important that such a
  <span>
   Time Source
  </span>
  uses
  <strong>
   seconds
  </strong>
  as its
  <a href="../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Time_Sources/Time_Source_Units.htm">
   unit
  </a>
  .
  <h4>
   Action Syntax:
  </h4>
  <br/><img src="https://gms.magecorn.com/Manual/assets/Images/Scripting_Reference/Drag_And_Drop/Reference/Time_Sources/Action_Syntax/BPM_to_Sec.png"/><br/>
  <h4>
   Arguments:
  </h4>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      Value
     </td>
     <td>
      The beats-per-minute value
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      Target
     </td>
     <td>
      The variable to store the returned seconds-per-beat value
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      Temp
     </td>
     <td>
      Whether the variable should be created as a temporary variable
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
 </body>
</html>